    • isWithinDistance

      private boolean isWithinDistance(InteractableObject obj)
      compute if player is near to an object or not. this is the logic that determines whether the player is near an object. called in updateCurrentInteractable()
      Parameters:
      obj - current interactable object
      Returns:
      true if the player is near enough, false otherwise

    • updateCurrentInteractable

      private boolean updateCurrentInteractable()
      check if player is near interactable object, sets the currentInteractable field if it is near. called in update() method
      Returns:
      true if isWithinDistance returns true and sets the currentInteractable, false if isWithinDistance returns false, and sets the currentInteractable to false
